author: rooneg
msg: * README
(EXAMPLE WALKTHROUGH): we don't have a handbook anymore, we have a book, so
let's point people to the right place when telling them to read to docs.

author: striker
msg: * subversion/include/svn_diff.h
(svn_diff3_file_output): Add a conflict_original argument.  Rename
other argument names to reflect the datasource of the conflict
section.  Add two flags: display_original_in_conflict and
display_resolved_conflicts.  These show all datasources in
a conflict block and displays commond diffs/true conflicts
respectively.  These are mutually exclusive: setting both
will behave as if only display_original_in_conflict was set.
* subversion/tests/libsvn_delta/diff3-test.c
(do_diff3): Update call to svn_diff3_file_output.
* subversion/libsvn_delta/diff_file.c
(svn_diff3__file_output_conflict): Make the output look more like the
output we are used to from diff3.  Add some standard error checking.
(svn_diff3_file_output): See comments above(svn_diff.h).

author: striker
msg: * subversion/libsvn_delta/diff.c
(svn_diff3): Enable the 'smart' conflict detection all the time.  This
effectively tries to find common differences in conflicts, returning
those and the true conflicts.  Remove the fallback code.

author: rooneg
msg: * subversion/libsvn_ra_svn/client.c
(ra_svn_open): remove initialization of tunnel_agent.
(find_tunnel_agent): initialize *agent in the error case, so the caller
doesn't have to worry about it.

author: rooneg
msg: * subversion/libsvn_ra_svn/client.c
(ra_svn_open): Initialize tunnel_agent before using it.
